Steps to Create IAM User
In search bar, type IAM and open
AWS Identity and Access Management

Create User
Click on “Users” (left panel)
Click “Create user”
Enter User Name
Example: dev-user

Set Permissions
Choose permission option:
Add user to group (recommended)
OR Attach policies directly
Select group or policy
Example: AdministratorAccess (full access)
OR limited access (best practice)

Access Type
Set password (auto/custom)

Review & Create
Click Next → Review
Click “Create user”

Save Credentials
Download or copy:
Username
Password
Access Key & Secret Key

Verify
Go to Users list → check created user






